me people say, “Never let them see you cry.” I say, if you’re so mad you could just cry, then cry. It terrifies everyone.\n\n- Tina Fey, Bossypants\n|\nHaving faith makes you vibrate at a frequency level that is identical to that of the universe, providing you a result that you would not have arrived at before.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Be First: Achieve Every Dream\n|\nAny coward can instill fear. It's easy to scare people, but having the strength to make them feel safe? Now that's power.\n\n- Nick\n|\nMusic is energy, emotion, expression, escapism, enlightenment. Music is so much more than just entertainment.\n\n- Rasheed\n|\nWhen people fall in love, they burst into flames.\n\n- Jandy Nelson, I'll Give You the Sun\n|\nYou fool, Helene. When you love, there is always more pain.\n\n- Sabaa Tahir, A Torch Against the Night\n|\nIf I had many who oppose me, it means I have stood for something sacred that only my heart knows.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWe’ are the self (chetan, Soul) and obstruction (antray) are non-self (achetan, non-Soul); therefore, the Self (chetan, Soul) shall win in the end!\n\n- Dada\n|\nGrowing up I often wondered how the world would be today if, since the beginning of human life, every person acted as I did.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nA child today, an adult tomorrow.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nEmmerich's heart in his throat, he could only stare down at Monica, who looked up at him with glassy eyes as she shivered with pain and choked on blood.\n\n- Suzanna J. Linton, Clara\n|\n...the simple task of getting dressed and undressed was a real strain, but nothing could compare with her addiction to deep sleep...\n\n- Ingeborg Bachmann, Simultan: Erzählungen\n|\nStyle never speaks, but somehow is always saying something.\n\n- Mircea\n|\nEverything was bright and white, even in the night.\n\n- Basma Salem, The Art Of Black\n|\nIn the fashion industry, everything goes retro except the prices.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nJesus also function on the earth through the power of light. Light, illumination, knowledge, insight, understanding, wisdom. That is their real power on earth\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIf you think people in your life are normal, then you undoubtedly have not spent any time getting to know the abnormal side of them.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nWhen you suspect old age is catching up with you, live faster!\n\n- Benny Bellamacina, Philosophical Uplifting Quotes volume 2\n|\nIf the gospel is old news to you, it will be dull news to everyone else.\n\n- Kevin\n|\nThe most important things are the hardest things to say, because words diminish them...\n\n- Stephen King, It\n|\nIn winter, on the darkest nights, one rejoices even to see the tiniest sliver of a moon.\n\n- Marty\n|\nLife has a purpose and that is to be happy, and happiness is the fruits of our love and labor.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf I have to die either for religion or atheism I would prefer atheism, since my conscience will respect my rational decision.\n\n- M.F.\n|\nWhen you relinquish the desire to control your future, you can have more happiness.\n\n- Nicole\n|\nShe imagined she could taste the storm in him, the battering winds of desperation and frustration that met her own, blow for blow.\n\n- Alexandra Bracken, Passenger\n|\nAfter all, plans are one thing; then the battle happens.\n\n- Aleksandra Layland, Of Wisdom and Valor: The Art of War. The Path of Peace.\n|\nThe longer you chase the wrong person, the further you travel in the wrong direction. You're better than that.\n\n- Steve\n|\nThey're the perfect loving fam'ly, so adoring...And I love them ev'ry day of ev'ry week.So my son's a little shit, my husband's boring,And my daughter, though a genius, is a freak.\n\n- Brian Yorkey, Next to Normal\n|\nHer heart kicked hard against her ribs, seized by a terrible fear that refused to let go no matter how hard she pushed.\n\n- Kady Cross, The Girl with the Windup Heart\n|\nThere's more than what the eye can see, the heart can love, and the brain can understand.\n\n- Louise\